    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, season the <strong>haddock bites </strong>(unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Once the rice is cooked, sit the <strong>haddock bites</strong> on top of the rice, then add a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, cover and cook for a further 3 min or until the haddock is cooked through – this is your <strong>one-pot</strong> <strong>gumbo-style spicy haddock</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
